David Keatts commented on [high] Weirdness with land counts and creature counts.: "scrapers are fixed up.  one of them wasn't reporting a basiccount at all, so it was defaulting to 0.  two of them were off-by-1 with the basic padding (padding up to 100 cards instead of 99 / 98).  also the code that was supposed to keep decks with <97 cards out of the db wasn't working.

ALSO you can now pass in deck urls to scrapers as command line arguments, useful for testing."
attachments.text:
scrapers are fixed up.  one of them wasn't reporting a basiccount at all, so it was defaulting to 0.  two of them were off-by-1 with the basic padding (padding up to 100 cards instead of 99 / 98).  also the code that was supposed to keep decks with <97 cards out of the db wasn't working.

ALSO you can now pass in deck urls to scrapers as command line arguments, useful for testing.

David Keatts commented on [high] Weirdness with land counts and creature counts.: "still need to fix all the bad decks in the db.  assuming we don't want to just delete a ton of decks and re-scrape, this is the soln I'm thinking of:

- make a copy of the deck db
- look through historical deck data. I'm thinking most of the decks scraped in the past X months have been incorrectly marked as 101-102 card decks, so if we care about avg land counts we should correct those
- find and delete all decks with creature count greater than actual number of creatures UNLESS it contains a relentless rat, shadowborn apostle, etc.

thoughts?"
